item.description:
arXiv:2606.02141v2 Announce Type: replace 
Abstract: In this article, we study the existence of normalized solutions to the following mixed nonlinear Choquard equation with exponential growth
  \begin{align*}
  \left\{
  \begin{aligned}
  \mathcal{L}u+\lambda u \; &=\; \Lambda(I_{\alpha}\ast F(u))F'(u), \quad \text{in }\mathbb{R}^{2},
  \int_{\mathbb{R}^{2}}|u|^{2}\,dx \; &=\; a^{2},
  \end{aligned}
  \right.
  \end{align*}
  where $\mathcal{L}= -\Delta+(-\Delta)^s$, $0<s<1$, $a>0$, $I_{\alpha}$ is the Riesz potential of order $\alpha\in (0,2)$, $\Lambda>0$ is a parameter and $\lambda\in \mathbb{R}$ appears as a Lagrange multiplier. Here, the nonlinearity $F$ has exponential growth in $\mathbb{R}^{2}$. Using variational methods, we prove the existence of normalized solution in the Poho\v{z}aev manifold. Moreover, we discuss the regularity result and the construction of the Poho\v{z}aev identity, essential for the existence.
  \keywords{Normalized solutions; Nonlinear Schr\"odinger equations; Choquard nonlinearity; Critical exponential growth; Trudinger-Moser inequality}
